 Q HOW do you  define grid columns and rows ?
. GRID the and columns and rows using the grid-template-columnsa and grid-template-rows properties
 . these proprties sepecify the size and numbers of coloums in the grid 
.container {
    display : grid; 
    grid-template-colums: 100px  20px;
}

Q What is the grid-template-columns property?
. The grid-template-columns proprty defines the number and width of columns in the grid 
. the width using unites like pixels(px), percentages(%), fractions(fr), or any other Css units 
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template: 1fr, 2fr, 1fr;
}

Q What is the grid -template-rows property?
. The grid-template-rows-property defines the number and hight of rows in the the grid.
. simliar to grid-template-columns , can specfiy the high using varible unites.

.container {
    display : grid;
    grid-template-rows: 100px 200px;
}

Q How do you create grid arease?
.Grid aresa are define using the grid-template ares property.
. area in areas in the grid and then assign the-area element to those using the grid-area property
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-area: "header header header"
                          "sideber content content"
                        " footer footer footer";
   grid-template-columns: 1fr, 3fr, 1fr;
   grid-template-rows: auto;
}

.header {
    grid-area: haeder;
}

.sodeber {
    grid-area: header;
}

.conter {
    grid-area: content;
}

.footer {
    grid-area: footer;
}

Q what is the grid-gap property 
.The grid-gap propert(now commonly) refferred to as gap deefines the spacing, between and columns in the grid.
.container {
    display; gird;
    gap: 10px;
}

Q How do you align items in a grid?
aling items in grid using  the following property: 
.justify-items: Aligns items :horizontally within their gird area.
align-tems : Aligns items :vertically within thier grid area
place-items: A shorthad for setting both justify-items and align-items
.container {
    display: grid;
    justify-items: center;
    align-items: center;
}

Q How do you create a reponsive grid layout?
.container {
    display : grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(100, 1fr));
    gap: 10px;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .container {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
}

RESPONSIVE DESIGN 
Q What is responsive design ?
.Responsive design is an apprach to web design that ensurse web pages render well on a variety of devices and window or screen sizes

Q What is Media Queries?
Media queries a CSS feature that allows  content rendering to adapt to different conditions such as screen size, resolutons, or orientations.
@media only screen and (max-width 600px) {
      body{
        background-color: lightbule;
      }
}


Q Explain how you can make images respaonvie using HTML and css. provide an example demonstrating differtent techniques such 
as the srcset attribute HTML and CSS properties?
. The Srcset attribute allows you to specfiy different images for different device width improving performance by serving most 
appropriate images
.in this example 
* Srcset specifies allows different for images files various width (300, 768w, 1200w)
* size defines the images display size based on the viewport width 
* Src provides a fallback images for browsers that do not support  Srcset 
<img 
    srcset = "
    small.jpg 300w,
    medium.jpg 768w,
    large.jpg 1200w"
    sizes = "
      (max-width: 600px) 300px,
      (max-width: 1200px) 768;
      1200px"
      src = "default.jpg"
      alt = " Responsive images">